The two authors are similar in many ways, one of them is that they both used pen names to write their stories. They also both performed the majority of their writing during times of strife in their own respective societies.

For Mark Twain, the majority of the conflict was occuring in the American South where racism was rampant. Twain made use of short stories and novels to document his views on racism in america and the affect it was having on the Amserican society. Sholem Aleichem's stories occured during a major pogralm in Russia during the 1700s.

Responding to the impact of technology on their own societies.
